699
00:54:52,155 --> 00:54:53,793
It would certainly be a story.

700
00:55:02,832 --> 00:55:07,747
I'm gonna tell you something
that I've never told anyone else,

701
00:55:09,939 --> 00:55:11,577
but I think you're ready to hear it.

702
00:55:13,610 --> 00:55:14,714
Okay.

703
00:55:17,814 --> 00:55:19,020
I'm not a puppet.

704
00:55:22,452 --> 00:55:23,726
I'm real.

705
00:55:25,922 --> 00:55:27,265
I'm alive.

706
00:55:28,291 --> 00:55:30,498
And the world needs to know.

707
00:55:52,315 --> 00:55:54,090
You all right, love?

708
00:55:57,420 --> 00:55:58,899
Some trouble?

709
00:55:59,656 --> 00:56:01,795
I talked to Dr. Macy today.

710
00:56:03,927 --> 00:56:06,464
What did he have to say for himself?

711
00:56:12,235 --> 00:56:14,977
He says that you haven't been to see him
in over a year.

712
00:56:16,639 --> 00:56:18,949
Dr. Macy says that you're sick, Walter.
Very sick.

713
00:56:19,008 --> 00:56:20,078
Yeah. Right.

714
00:56:20,143 --> 00:56:22,054
He said this sounds like
some kind of a mania.

715
00:56:22,112 --> 00:56:25,218
Okay, well, who gives a shit
what Dr. Macy has to say?

716
00:56:25,281 --> 00:56:26,282
I fixed him.

717
00:56:27,283 --> 00:56:32,062
Everybody else seems to get it.
Henry, people at work. Everyone except you.

718
00:56:33,289 --> 00:56:34,359
Does that tell you something?

719
00:56:34,424 --> 00:56:36,631
You just want to live like this forever?
Talking through your hand?

720
00:56:36,693 --> 00:56:39,606
I'd say it's been a pretty
smashing success so far, wouldn't you?

721
00:56:39,662 --> 00:56:43,075
